posts.subject: ATF Agent tased, arrested at gunpoint by Columbus Police - new bodycam footage
posts.body:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=gb1MVFDy_tw

News2Share has obtained previously unreleased footage of a July 7, 2020 incident in which ATF Agent James Burk attempted to make contact with a member of the Columbus, Ohio community, who then called 911.

When Columbus PD officers Joseph Fihe and Kevin Winchell arrived, Agent Burk did not comply with their commands, even at gunpoint. The officers tased Agent Burk in the process of subduing him.

Agent Burk - who in 2015 was charged with shoplifting wine from a Kroger grocery story - is now suing the officers for excessive force.

posts.subject: Your Feds at work
posts.body: Why can't we terminate all of them?

>>29cd786b-7e03-4cca-8172-560b66cc5af1
All they do is lose wars and engage in turfwars.

>>5e2b1fce-6b59-4c1c-bd63-7b217838ff74
Hollywood. But it does suggest that targets at distance are better engaged with scoped rifles.

Imagine what a highly tuned varmint rifle could do vs armored Orcs. Some of those rifles are capable of repeatable 1in groups at 200 yds.

Projectiles are lightweight - so limited. Some method must be found for making use of powerful street poisons like fentanyl with rifles serving as the delivery system.

The Europeans were using push bolt actions over a hundred years ago. This American design looks to be better :)

posts.subject: Ex-Marine and Neo-Nazi Told Followers How to Shoot Truckers to Dismantle Supply Chain
posts.body:
Reasonable critique of "the plan".

Those 25 would need to be highly focused on opposition strongholds, while "rest of the country" basked in complete peace. Complete peace.

There should never be any reason for the 98% to turn on the 2% partisans. That's suicide. Think farmers ambushing gunslingers once they leave town. This issue is never discussed enough. Just what do you say to the losers in these battles? The white people losing everything to riots within those cities. Sniping works both ways. You never wish to be on the wrong side of public sentiment. They CAN do something about it.

And the cities you target? Better have a workable plan to prevent those people from escaping into the hinterland. That cannot be allowed. Likely would require that permanent damage be inflicted upon the fuel supply.

This plan is very similar to the power grid takedown. Hard to imagine something which would piss off normies more....

"Acceleration" sorely needs a plan for the AFTER. Otherwise it's as incompetent as "Whut we got".

Maybe a good start? Restoration of civil liberties coupled with mass removal of troublemakers. You might gain a consensus with that.  A consensus is needed because US citizens are armed.

And no need for ethnostates if you've captured the entire country. Think big.

How many normies can be "switched" if their lives improve? Right now productive citizens are second class citizens. Surely that's a reality to exploit? Make citizenship mean something again!

Just banning both the Democrat and Republican parties would buy you a lot of goodwill. Both are traitorous cesspools. And imagine the public glee if both tech and media operatives found themselves permanently in Gitmo.

posts.subject: I don't know what to think any more ....
A disaster
posts.body:
Imagine teaching racism against blacks in public schools. Would that be tolerated?


Eventual consequences I see from this?


Effective defunding of all public schools. Parents will place their kids within explicitly white schools ONLY, and all teacher contracts will be "at will".

The rigor of these "new schools created" will eventually achieve 1901 levels......


"Shadow public schools" will continue to operate for some time, but the standards will be lowered and lowered until such schools become meaningless and die of their own accord.



The experiment is over. Everyone knows the result. Someone must do the work. That's a non negotiable outcome. We've already lost unrecoverable training time due to foily and covid. Workplace competence will take yet another hit.

Watch those teachers scream when they get Patcoed......They should have seen it coming.

posts.subject: How many Democrats are driven away by these idiots?
posts.body:
OTOH, defunding the police would be no problem in red states. Things would be settled quickly.


White House Gets 'Three Pinocchios' for claiming Republicans are defunding police Anonymous 07/07/21(Wed)16:14:32 No.884203▶>>884235

    The Washington Post's Fact-Checker dinged the White House for claiming Republicans were "defunding the police," giving the eyebrow-raising talking point "Three Pinocchios."

    Recent remarks by White House Press Secretary Jen Psaki and senior Biden adviser Cedric Richmond had sought to turn the tables on months of some progressive Democrats advocating for slicing or even dismantling municipal police department budgets. Their logic was GOP opposition to the $1.9-trillion coronavirus relief bill passed this year amounted to supporting defunding police, since $350 billion was allocated for state and local government aid.

    "Although Republicans all opposed Biden’s coronavirus relief package, no one voted to cut, or defund, anything. Rather, Democrats proposed $350 billion in emergency funds for state and local governments, and Republicans voted against those extra funds. That’s not a reduction," the Post's Glenn Kessler wrote.

    MEDIA FALL IN LINE WITH PSAKI'S CLAIM REPUBLICANS WANT TO DEFUND THE POLICE: ‘SIMPLY PREPOSTEROUS’

    President Biden has resisted efforts from the left flank of his party to call for police budget cuts, but the efforts by his White House to shift the label of anti-police to Republicans appeared to demonstrate the damage of even the appearance of that position. Despite the brazenness of the White House's claims, some liberal media figures fell in line with the talking point, Fox News reported last week.

    https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2021/07/07/white-houses-slipshod-claim-that-republicans-are-defunding-police/

    https://www.factcheck.org/2021/07/democrat-makes-misleading-defund-the-police-claim/
    https://www.foxnews.com/media/washington-post-white-house-three-pinocchios-republicans-defunding-police

Liberal cities bathing in blood Anonymous 07/06/21(Tue)00:06:32 No.883271▶>>883273 >>883511 >>883604 >>883687 >>883740 >>884249

    379 shot.
    142 dead.
    Every city in the top 10 is progressive.
    https://www.tech-gate.org/usa/2021/07/06/independence-day-bloodbath-379-are-shot-142-fatally-across-us-over-july-4-weekend/

    Independence Day bloodbath: 379 are shot – 142 fatally – across US Over holiday

    US streets were bathed in blood over Independence Day weekend with 142 killed in 379 separate shootings, with Chicago and Philadelphia among the locations worst-hit.

    Chicago suffered the greatest bloodshed, with at least 92 shootings over the long weekend. That saw 16 killed and 76 injured.


    Ramirez told ABC 7 that her brother was gunned down in a drive-by shooting when he went outside to grab something. A motive is unclear.

    Others who survived shootings in the Windy City included children as young as five and six, with others shot in the 12 to 30 age bracket, the Chicago Sun Times, reported.

    Two cops were among the city’s shooting victims. The unidentified officers were shot in the early hours of Monday while trying to disperse a crowd in the city’s Washington Park.

    They were rushed to hospital, and are expected to survive their injuries.

    Philadelphia saw a total of 17 people shot over the weekend, with 21 injured, and seven killed.

    Eleven people were shot, four died and another was stabbed during a six hour orgy of violence in Philadelphia during July 4 celebrations.

    Six of those 11 shot were teenagers aged between 15 and 19.

    The grim toll included a double murder where more than 100 shots rang out.

    Shortly after 10:30pm on Sunday, more than 100 bullets ripped through a West Philadelphia barbeque, hitting 22-year-old Sincarr Johnson Jr. in the head, a 23-year-old man multiple times in the torso and a 16-year-old girl in the butt and leg.

    Johnson Jr. and the 23-year-old, who hasn’t been identified, died. The teenager is in stable condition, police said.

    On Saturday, three people were fatally shot, including a six-year-old boy in the Northeast section of the city.

posts.subject: Someday we'll learn.....
posts.body:
How this racist government seized power...

Their policies make no sense - unless they are doing the bidding of others.

posts.subject: It's time for all of this to stop.
posts.body:
No more gibs. None of it.

Put their kids in prison early.

Antiwhite racism - just say no!

The global cinema industry is set to lose $32 billion in 2020 due to the COVID-19 pandemic, a 71.5% reduction in box office revenue compared to 2019, according to a recent report by media and tech research firm Omdia.

In a deadly shootout, J.C barely manages to escape with his life. He retreats, pursued by a gender diverse and multicultural army.

posts.body:
The Oklahoma castle doctrine or stand your ground laws permit a person to the ability to utilize what is known as reasonable force to protect his or her person. This can include the use of deadly force is the situation warrants this type of lethal response.


Protecting yourself in your home and outside of your home

The stand your ground laws in Oklahoma are broad in their scope and application. Not only can you invoke the provisions of the castle doctrine in your home, but Oklahoma law also maintains that you have the legal ability to stand your ground when you are away from your residence. In other words, if you face a threat to your personal safety outside of your home, you have the ability to respond with force, including deadly force if reasonably deemed to be necessary. Pursuant to Oklahoma law, you are not obliged to flee the scene if your personal safety is threatened.

posts.subject: The current education minister of South Africa

posts.body:
>>088878bb-8756-42ea-8f4e-0408b15c9bd6
Mostly just "too busy" with other things I suspect.  So the problem gets tossed in the "todo" bin - but never gets fixed. 

Discipline is simple. Don't watch their programs. Don't buy from their advertisers.

If someone could come up with an easy way to track advertisers for targeting - it would do a great deal of good.

And why haven't truthful news networks been formed to talk advantage of this situation? No money in it?

This is "mission accomplished" bullshit. Khan would never relax until his enemies could never strike again.

>>1170b32e-d3f9-4b52-b351-7d1c0f67faac
Just helping out...

Following clearnet links from a secure network can be problematic. It's much safer to play videos directly from Zeronet, and anything harvested from the clearnet should always be performed with maximum obfuscation (multiple VPNs with no financial trackback to you).

Biden clearly knows he's not up to the job. So what is his motivation here? Very curious. Is it simply his hatred for Trump is that strong? Or something else?

Trump was also a disappointment on many levels. Even something as simple as releasing the JFK files? That sure was memory holed quick?

So much going on in government makes no sense. Unless clues/facts are being kept from us.

posts.subject: Canada must be a lawless place ......
posts.body:
Where any official can make up the rules as they go along.

More persuaded by the idea that until there is a marriage contract - zero obligations exist. If a woman can't secure such a contract - perhaps she should refrain from spreading her legs? 

Soooo many social problems can be directly traced to the weaking of contracts and private behavior. The state has no role here - excepting the enforcement of those contracts.

posts.body:
>>1e705e61-ea70-4e4b-9486-dd3e5f00c5cd
Right now, believe most people are using telegram for such banter. It's kinda like having 42 wrenches in your garage capable of pulling a bolt. Invariably, over time, you'll focus on those few wrenches which best fit your task.

Zeronet is hard for many to setup. It still has bugs, and requires significant CPU. And ZeroId is a real barrier, oftentimes so cantankerous many give up. So those people just lurk and download. Not worth the squeeze for them to learn how to trick Zeronet into working.

This might change over time, because ZeroNet's "killer app" potential is secure bittorrent. There is probably NOTHING out there as efficient. But even there, why has no one built a simple SQlite based image manager specifically for Millchan to ease the cataloging of images? I've done this with Shotwell as an experiment. It works very well. Shotwell never touches the originals, and quickly generates a "map" of your images. The one problem I see is that it also indexes the icons Millchan stores to enable browser access.

The final problem is just numbers. When many seeders are online - Zeronet can be very fast. Approaching server client speeds. But this rarely happens because few run their servers more than a few hours a day.

Without buy in by normies willing to spend some money to support their freedoms - Zeronet will never achieve it's potential. Frankly, the trend looks kinda soft after the election. Seeders are still out there - but in nowhere near the same numbers. Just before the election Zeronet was VERY fast.

If twofish had used one of the newer hashes like Blake...Zeronet might have been shoehorned into garbage hardware - making it more accessible. Reality is we'll be lucky if the author even continues his "charitable coding".  This Tor V3 changeover could break ZeroNet.

posts.subject: The issue of our time
posts.body:
Made worse by a quote now ringing in my ears:

"Nothing changes until someone dies."

posts.subject: I have the greatest respect for content creators....
posts.body:
But they must stop being shit-for-brains!

ANYTHING which might be censored (just about anything now) should be posted to ZeroNet FIRST. Zeronet should always be their first stop.

posts.subject: I was irritated when they stormed the Capitol...
posts.body:
Reeked like that left wing sit-in inside Nancy's office. Thought then (as I do now), that Nancy and clones should have pulled out their ARs and just started blasting. No prisoners! :)

Similarly, that bunch breaking into the Capitol should have been attacked instantly. Not surprising to me that the Capitol police has been niggered :(

Fast forward to this pious posturing by Democrats after they let TWO groups invade them and are allowing foreigners to invade us right now? 

Nope. Now wish that Capitol bunch DID have a plan. Wish they had come armed and ready for business - with the sole aim of killing every official they could find. None of them would have ultimately survived this assault. It would have been a one way ticket to hell with an honor guard of worthless Congressmen. And I wish every single one of them had fully understood this going in.

Waco - in our time. Real deal.

Why? Might have given our population the grit to finally settle these old scores and clean out the many old mistakes. Those sacrificed during the Capitol assault would have triggered that larger war.

As it stands now, the Democrats will crucify these people for stupid Larping. What a waste. At least go out after slaying all your enemies and making sure they can never fight you again? These Larpers have zero scalps - and they have surrendered. Basic rules were never followed. Like you NEVER get into that car with your kidnapper?

You can't cheat an honest man, and you can't bargain with someone with nothing to lose who truly intends to kill you. 

Capitol invaders, you failed to die well. Now you will know purest hell.

Davidians did it right. Their only failure was that not enough ATF people went with them.

"And how we burned in the camps later, thinking: What would things have been like if every Security operative, when he went out at night to make an arrest, had been uncertain whether he would return alive and had to say good-bye to his family? Or if, during periods of mass arrests, as for example in Leningrad, when they arrested a quarter of the entire city, people had not simply sat there in their lairs, paling with terror at every bang of the downstairs door and at every step on the staircase, but had understood they had nothing left to lose and had boldly set up in the downstairs hall an ambush of half a dozen people with axes, hammers, pokers, or whatever else was at hand?… The Organs would very quickly have suffered a shortage of officers and transport and, notwithstanding all of Stalin’s thirst, the cursed machine would have ground to a halt! If…if…We didn’t love freedom enough." 

Aleksandr I. Solzhenitsyn

posts.body:

Never did really understand the motivation of those kicking alphabets....they are a pitiful lot. Kicking them was like kicking a cripple.....

But now that the LGBTs have managed to shit up the real world so bad - it's time to seriously entertain the idea of killing them and all their enablers.

After the first LGBT you kill - the next are easier.

I hear that baker in Colorado who was almost ruined by a previous lawsuit now has two new tormentors. There may come a day when people routinely grant relief to such victims - by simply killing off their enemies.

Dead people don't sue.
